tags.description: WSW facing, good for Winter afternoons or Summer mornings. Gets sun from 1 pm. 3 slabby cliff areas from 8 - 20 m high.Great bouldering on slightly overhung rock on the up-hill side of the cliffs.The rock quality is generally friable and can be mossy.
tags.name: Pine Rocks

tags.description: The pick of the climbing in the area. Two pinnacles. Scramble to get to top. The scramble up the bigger (left) pinnacle is a bit tricky and exposed. Top-rope anchors in-situ on top of both pinnacles.
tags.name: Left Side

tags.description: Roof and Slab. Again plenty of loose rock so bring brush and cleaning will be involved till we get more traffic.
tags.name: Lower Lefter Side

tags.description: Main Wall is the best and most concentrated bouldering area. Slightly overhung.
tags.name: Main Bouldering Wall

tags.description: Scramble around for a bit of a warm up. Left side more slabby, right side traverse is fun. Continue through to get to Main Bouldering Wall.
tags.name: Warmup Alley

tags.description:
Right hand side of Pine Rocks climbing area.
Slabby and highly featured, some loose rock.
tags.name: Right Side

tags.description: Low angle, easy routes. Good for early beginners. Bring a brush.
tags.name: Back Slab

tags.description: The isolated pinnacle at the centre of the crag. Escape off the back using the two small jugs to rig an abseil (hang rope off one and back up with an in-situ cord looped around the other.
tags.name: Central Pinnacle

tags.description: Up prominent rib on left side of cliff. (FFA literally his first ever lead climb)
tags.name: My First Lead Climb

tags.description:
Hard low crux protected by second bolt. Not over once you get established above it and clip the 3rd.

tags.name: Share the love

tags.description: Line of SS carrot bolts that trends right midway up the cliff. Looks like was originally carrots (glued in threaded bolts with nut) for lower off/walk off. Can just lower of anchors on the next route to the right.
tags.name: Up the Guts

tags.description: Low protected crux where you run out of feet.
tags.name: Bitter Sweet

tags.description: Slabby face 4m left of Central Crack. Thin and technical, fun climbing. Escape left to arete when the face blanks out.
tags.name: Left Slab
